    thinking: "**Analyzing the User\'s Request**\n\nI\'m digging into the user\'s request, focusing on the specific flow they described: User Login -> Dashboard -> Nav Item Selection. I understand they want to make sure specific navigation items function as expected, such as \"Danh m\341\273\245c ti\303\252u ch\303\255\".\n\n\n**Defining the Core Workflow**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the CRUD operations for criteria and the report management flow. I\'m visualizing CRUD for reports, with the ability to view details, like a specific \"NTM Report\" displaying forms 04-13. From there, I\'m thinking, selecting a form reveals its details, and the flow proceeds through report submission, validation, and supervision.\n\n\n**Mapping Navigation and Actions**\n\nI\'m now concretely mapping navigation menu items to specific actions within the user\'s defined flow. I have identified \"Danh m\341\273\245c ti\303\252u ch\303\255,\" associated with CRUD operations for criteria. \"Qu\341\272\243n l\303\275 \304\221\341\273\243t b\303\241o c\303\241o\" links to report period management, encompassing both CRUD actions and period detail viewing. \"Xem chi ti\341\272\277t \304\221\341\273\243t\" focuses on displaying form details; for instance, \"\304\221\341\273\243t b\303\241o c\303\241o NTM\" showing and selecting \"bi\341\273\203u 04-13.\" Selecting these forms should then reveal their detailed tables, with a flow leading into report submission, and validation.\n\n\n**Defining Form Status Transitions**\n\nI\'m now detailing the form status workflow: Draft -> Sent -> Appraised -> Supervised. I\'m focusing on \"G\341\273\255i b\303\241o c\303\241o,\" transitioning forms to \"\304\220\303\243 g\341\273\255i,\" which will be triggered by a \"Send\" action. Then, \"Th\341\272\251m \304\221\341\273\213nh\" (Appraisal) will be handled by provincial officials, and will result in approval or rejection, with the form changing to \"\304\220\303\243 th\341\272\251m \304\221\341\273\213nh.\" Lastly, \"Gi\303\241m s\303\241t\" (Supervision) allows supervisors to log comments, and transition the form status to \"\304\220\303\243 gi\303\241m s\303\241t\" or \"Ho\303\240n th\303\240nh gi\303\241m s\303\241t\".\n\nI am going to then map this workflow out into a full application flow.\nI will change `/src/types.ts` and `/src/mockData.ts` to support this enhanced data model and state transitions, and I plan to modify `/src/App.tsx` or create new components to make this app flow really pop!\n\n\n**Revising Data Models**\n\nI\'m now revising the data models for reporting periods and forms, looking closely at `/src/types.ts`. I\'m structuring a \"reporting period\" with id, name, year, status, and associated forms. The \"form\" will include a code, title, status, and the criteria data, simplifying criteria management. I am thinking this is a good first step!\n\n\n**Designing Role-Based Access**\n\nI\'m now designing a mock system with role-based access to facilitate testing the entire workflow. The idea is to enable easy role switching - either via a role selector on the dashboard or by logging in with preset roles. This interactive design will allow seamless testing of the full CRUD, submission, appraisal, and monitoring flows. I will also check for necessary package installations.\n\n\n"
