" status. I\'m excited about this robust implementation that fulfills the business flow!\n\n\n**Enriching the Data Types**\n\nI\'m expanding the data types now. I\'m adding `Criterion`, `ReportPeriod`, `FormReport`, `AppraisalLog`, `SupervisionLog`, and `UserSession` to `types.ts`, which currently runs to line 57. My goal is to create a robust single source of truth for all of our models in the backend. I\'m implementing models for each form to manage the appraisal and supervision states effectively.\n\n\n**Drafting the New Models**\n\nI\'m now drafting the models that will represent the core data structures. I\'ve focused on `Criterion`, `AppraisalLog`, `SupervisionLog`, and `FormReport` interfaces. These interfaces define the basic structure for important features, and I\'ve also drafted a `CriterionValueRow` interface for the detail screen.\n\n\n**Refining Existing Types**\n\nOkay, I\'m now refining the existing data types to ensure compatibility and consistency. I\'m adding `CriterionValueRow` to the existing types, as the types are imported in existing components. I have carefully inspected `OverviewTab.tsx`, `ReportTab.tsx`, and `StatisticsTab.tsx` to assess the impact of these changes.\n\n\n"
