  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Developing Extended Models**\n\nI\'ve successfully extended the models in `types.ts` and `mockData.ts`. Now, the focus is shifting towards developing a clean login interface. Next, I need to design full-fidelity screens, including the \"Danh m\341\273\245c ti\303\252u ch\303\255\" section (with CRUD) and the \"Qu\341\272\243n l\303\275 \304\221\341\273\243t\" section.\n\n\n**Designing Appraisal Flow**\n\nI\'m now diving into the \"b\303\241o c\303\241o\" section, aiming for CRUD functionality and detailed viewing. I\'ve outlined the report forms from \"Bi\341\273\203u 04\" to \"Bi\341\273\203u 13\" and their display under a selected \"\304\221\341\273\243t b\303\241o c\303\241o.\" I\'m also planning the design for the form details, including an input table, drag-and-drop for proofs, and a send button.\nI\'ll also need to model the appraisal and supervision flow actions for different roles. I am designing a login view and the initial navigation flow, integrating the \"Danh m\341\273\245c ti\303\252u ch\303\255\" and \"Qu\341\272\243n l\303\275 \304\221\341\273\243t b\303\241o c\303\241o\" sections. I am also planning the detailed view with forms and the appraisal / supervision actions!\n\n\n**Implementing Core Features**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the login screen with role selection and credential input. I\'ll then move to implementing CRUD operations for criteria within `CriteriaTab.tsx`, allowing for adding, editing, and deleting criteria. Finally, I\'ll tackle the `ReportPeriodsTab.tsx`, enabling full CRUD functionality for reporting periods and a detailed view linking to specific forms like \"Bi\341\273\203u 04\" to \"Bi\341\273\203u 13\".\n\n\n**Refining Form Interactions**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the `FormDetailView.tsx` component. I\'m structuring it to handle detailed form entry, including a dynamic table of criteria, cell value modifications with flashing effects, and an evidence uploader. My current thoughts are on implementing the \"K\303\275 s\341\273\221 & G\341\273\255i b\303\241o c\303\241o\" button, updating the form status to \"SUBMITTED\" upon submission. I\'m also considering the design for `AppraisalSupervisionTab.tsx` and how to integrate appraisal and supervision actions seamlessly within the form detail view. I\'m leaning toward putting these action panels in the header/footer of the `FormDetailView.tsx` when the form is submitted or approved, to create an intuitive user flow.\n\n\n**Unifying Report Management**\n\nI\'m now fully committed to integrating all report period and form interactions within `ReportTab.tsx`. This includes selecting active reporting periods, displaying form lists (04-13) with status and actions, and rendering the dynamic form details upon selection. The form view will encompass interactive criteria tables, evidence upload, and role-based action buttons (\"G\341\273\255i b\303\241o c\303\241o\", \"Th\341\272\251m \304\221\341\273\213nh\", \"Gi\303\241m s\303\241t\").\n\n\n"
