    thinking: "**Prioritizing Reporting Periods**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the CRUD operations for Reporting Periods, as that seems like a foundational step. I\'ll start by creating the `/src/components/ReportPeriodsTab.tsx` file, using `create_file`. Building out the CRUD functions first should provide a good base. This should encompass features related to \"qu\341\272\243n l\303\275 \304\221\341\273\243t b\303\241o\".\n\n\n**Defining Period CRUD Workflow**\n\nI\'ve decided to refine the `ReportPeriodsTab.tsx` component\'s functionality to directly support Period CRUD operations. The crucial workflow involves \"Xem chi ti\341\272\277t \304\221\341\273\243t\" to view forms 04-13. Selecting a period row renders a list of the associated forms. Clicking a form then opens the detailed view for that particular form, where the data, evidence files and the sending workflow can be managed.\n\n\n**Designing Report Periods Tab**\n\nI\'m now designing the `ReportPeriodsTab` component, prioritizing a responsive and user-friendly interface. It\'ll handle creating, editing, and deleting periods, and viewing period details. The detail view will showcase form headers, stats, and a list of forms with codes, titles, statuses, update dates, and actions. Selecting \"Xem chi ti\341\272\277t\" will trigger a callback. I have confirmed that the `FORM_METAS` in `src/mockData.ts` includes the necessary form entries and that the function `createDefaultFormsForPeriod(periodId)` will be able to create the fully customized `FormReport`s.\n\n\n"
