    thinking: "**Assessing Interface Simplicity**\n\nI\'ve homed in on the UI\'s simplicity. I\'m getting a sense that it might be perceived as a bit unpolished. It lacks refined layouts, styled elements, and has a rather dry feel to it, relying heavily on standard grey blocks and repetitive components. I\'m focusing on why it might come across this way.\n\n\n**Elevating Visual Appeal**\n\nI\'m now diving into visual enhancements. I\'m aiming for exceptional aesthetics, drawing inspiration from high-end SaaS platforms and elegant government dashboards. I\'ve broken down key areas: refined typography and hierarchy with clean uppercase sub-elements; prominent branding with the government crest enhanced with gradients; a premium login screen design using dark, elegant themes, glassmorphism, and glowing edges; and a sophisticated sidebar to elevate its visual appeal.\n\n\n**Refining Dashboard Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on UI components. The sidebars deserve a luxurious treatment \342\200\223 envisioning Vietnamese national colors, such as deep crimson or navy, elegantly rendered with glassmorphism, subtle active states, and a custom brand banner. Report cards need a premium feel, akin to elegant dashboard blocks, with delicate progression indicators and refined visual cues. The Bi\341\273\203u 04-13 list demands a makeover for a beautifully organized, searchable, and filtered format.\n\n\n**Enhancing Data Presentation**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on data visualization and presentation improvements. I\'m focusing on creating clean, color-coded group summaries with \"nh\303\263m\" banners, and integrating Excel-like functionality. This includes hover rows, striped backgrounds, inline status controls, elegant tooltips, fast fill options, and an audit log timeline. I\'m also planning a gorgeous drag-and-drop file upload experience with real-time indicators, verification panels with legal stamps, and detailed metadata. Finally, I\'m working to make a fantastic hero banner, featuring deep gradients, floating SVGs, and glassmorphic data highlights. I\'ll make the charts pop.\n\n\n**Optimizing Statistical Displays**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the \"Ph\303\242n b\341\273\225 Ti\303\252u chu\341\272\251n theo Nh\303\263m X\303\243\" section, aiming for elegant card displays with icons and a \"Bento grid\" aesthetic. The Statistics Tab demands multi-dimensional comparative metrics with custom bar styling. I\'m focusing on enhancements like rich indicators, rounded corners, and a loading indicator for the Excel export. Now, I will view `LoginScreen.tsx` to get this upgrade started.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 535529091
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
