  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Upgrading the Product**\n\nI\'m focusing on elevating the product\'s quality. Specifically, the sidebar needs a significant visual overhaul. Currently, the plain white background and basic icons and buttons aren\'t cutting it. I\'m thinking of a deep royal navy or national color scheme to give it a premium feel.\n\n\n**Revising Visuals**\n\nI\'ve shifted focus to a governmental dark theme for the sidebar, specifically a deep navy blend like `#0a1c36` or `#0c192c`, aiming for a professional feel. The logo will receive a radial backglow, and the \"N\303\264ng th\303\264n m\341\273\233i\" text should glow in elegant gold. Menu button enhancements include border-left details, active gradients, and subtle hover states. I\'m also planning a stunning translucent acrylic login card with glowing borders for the login screen.\n\n\n**Refining Interface Elements**\n\nI\'m now implementing gold focus highlights for input fields, designing a high-resolution visual layout, and crafting clear role indicators to achieve an authentic enterprise software feel. Specifically, the login cards will utilize translucent glass-morphism effects with subtle backdrops and refined border treatments. I\'m also revising the main banner with a rich gradient and refined vector backgrounds, elegant KPIs, and custom Recharts with sleek gradients and soft glows.\n\n\n**Enhancing Card Design**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the visual upgrade of period navigation card blocks, aiming for a sleek look with rounded edges, glass headers, gradient progress bars, and clean indicator widgets. I\'ll implement status badges to convey drafts, submissions, approvals, and supervisions. The Form indices grid will be updated with a modern, dense list design, clear completion rates, and dynamic role indicators.\n\\n\\n\n**Improving Data Entry**\n\nNow I\'m looking at FormDetailView.tsx, specifically the data entry tables. I plan to style the number input fields for a more premium feel, with centered text, soft borders, group-based colored focus glows (slate blue, rose, emerald), and row highlights. I\'m also planning a sticky header for better context, and a quick action button for fast sample data input.\n\n\n**Designing Login Screen**\n\nI\'m now diving into `/src/components/LoginScreen.tsx`. My goal is a stunning state-of-the-art visual theme. I\'m focusing on crafting a deep radial navy-indigo background, representing Vietnam\'s rural-to-modern transition. For the login cards, I\'m using sleek frosted-glass acrylic with luminous gold and emerald status bars, all typed in \"Space Grotesk.\" I\'m also planning an elegant \"Digital CA certified\" banner with legal details and a green seal for the file uploader, to look professional. I\'m also thinking of how to make approval commentary and rating look neat, like a modern workflow block.\n\n\n"
